2:32 PM Defendant David A Nelson in court.  Attorney Thomas J McClure Esq in court for David A Nelson. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Abigail Kincheloe. 
Cases called for plea and sentencing.
State has complied with victim's rights. 
State has filed an Amended Information in 22CF360.
Defense acknowledges receipt of Amended Information and waives reading.  
NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.                                          
State places offer on the record. 
Defendant has paid requested restitution of $2,940 in full. 
Court conducts plea colloquy.

In case 22CF360: 
Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Amended Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty. 
Case 22CF363 is Dismissed outright. 
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.

Court orders the following:
WITHHELD SENTENCE
3 Days Credit if revoked; 

TERM ON PROBATION:   2 YEARS; 
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by treatment providers; 
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Community Service: 80 Hours; 
*No operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant's father consents and the agent approves; 

RESTITUTION:  Paid in Full;
COSTS:  $243
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all restitution/costs/fees, and no new law violations. If the Defendant violates any terms of his/her probation, or has any condition time imposed, the Court will deem that the conditions precedent necessary for the conditional grant of Expunction have not been met and therefore Expunction is denied. The defendant shall file a petition with the Court to verify the successful completion of the sentence.
